column5: Pulled our hut off last saturday . didn;t get much use unfortunatly . Brother laws sled belw up early winter and too far for me to just 'pop' out to ( Barrie to Beaverton)  In case you are worried 20" of good hard ice !      welcome Wallmart shoppers    Bring on the thaw !  TB
These 90-100k wind gusts may be removing huts as I type.  I'm with you on the thaw, lets get 'er done.
no kidding I walked out in thE last rain/wind storm to anchor the darn thing . would have been gone for sure.  TB
Good job TB! Hundreds of huts were taken off the Larry last weekend. It always reminds me of Del Shannon's old classic "Huts off the Larry".
Good you got it off when you did, things are unpredictable now....only saw one hut left on Penetang Bay today...  Maureen
